Data Distribution Analysis using Python
This project analyzes data distribution using Python. 
It generates synthetic datasets for two groups, visualizes their distributions with histograms and boxplots, and computes descriptive statistics. 
The goal is to demonstrate data visualization and basic statistical analysis using pandas, numpy, matplotlib, and seaborn.

Features
Synthetic Data Generation: Creates two normally distributed datasets representing Group A and Group B.
Histogram with KDE: Plots overlapping histograms with Kernel Density Estimation to compare distributions.
Boxplot Analysis: Identifies outliers and compares data spread across groups.
Descriptive Statistics: Outputs summary statistics and skewness for each group.Automatic Export: Saves generated plots as PNG files for reporting.
Language: Python 3.8+
Libraries: pandas, numpy, matplotlib, seaborn



